<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <meta name="description" content="Frequently asked questions about visa processing, document attestation, and business setup in UAE.">
  <title>FAQ - VistaDocs Center</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/img/identity.png">
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/img/identity.png">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header') %>
  
  <main>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="page-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Common questions about visa and document services in UAE</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      
      <div class="faq-category">
        <h2>Visa Processing</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How long does employment visa processing take?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Standard employment visa processing takes 7 to 14 working days from document submission to residence visa stamping, excluding medical tests and Emirates ID processing.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What is the minimum salary required for family sponsorship?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Minimum salary requirements vary by nationality and emirate, typically AED 4,000 or AED 10,000 plus accommodation allowance or AED 3,000 additional.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can I extend my tourist visa while in UAE?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes, 30-day tourist visas can be extended once for an additional 30 days. Extension applications must be submitted before the original visa expires.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What is the minimum property value for Golden Visa eligibility?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Property must be valued at AED 2 million or above for Golden Visa eligibility. Off-plan properties may qualify under specific conditions set by authorities.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-category">
        <h2>Document Attestation</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How long does document attestation take?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Attestation timelines depend on the issuing country and document type. Typically 15 to 25 working days. UAE-issued documents can be attested within 3 to 7 days.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Do I need to attest documents from my home country first?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes, documents issued outside UAE must first be attested by your home country authorities and UAE embassy before MOFA attestation in the UAE.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can I attest photocopies or do I need originals?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Original documents are required for attestation. Certified copies may be accepted in some cases, but originals are always recommended to avoid rejection.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-category">
        <h2>Labour and Immigration</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How long is a labour card valid in UAE?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Labour cards are typically valid for 2 years and must be renewed before expiry to avoid penalties for both employer and employee.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What tests are included in the medical fitness examination?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Medical fitness tests include blood tests for infectious diseases, chest X-ray screening, and general physical examination as per UAE health authority requirements.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How long is Emirates ID valid?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Emirates ID validity matches residence visa validity, typically 2 or 3 years. Renewal must be completed within 30 days of visa renewal to avoid fines.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-category">
        <h2>Business Setup</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Do I need a local sponsor for mainland company setup?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>As of 2021, 100% foreign ownership is allowed for most business activities, eliminating the need for a local sponsor. A local service agent is required for certain activities only.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Can a free zone company trade in UAE mainland?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Free zone companies can trade in UAE mainland by appointing a local distributor or obtaining a mainland trade license as an additional service.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What is the difference between in-house PRO and outsourced PRO services?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>In-house PROs are company employees handling only that company's government transactions. Outsourced PRO services are external professionals serving multiple clients with expertise across various government departments.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-category">
        <h2>General Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">What are your service fees?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Service fees vary by service type and complexity. Contact us for a detailed quotation based on your specific requirements.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">Do you offer express or urgent processing?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes, express processing services are available for most visa and document services, subject to government department availability and additional fees.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <h3 class="faq-question">How can I track my application status?</h3>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Once your application is submitted, we provide regular status updates via email and phone. You can also contact our team directly for immediate updates.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
  </main>
  
  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
